net.sf.jclec.mo.comparator

Class ConstrainedComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.comparator.MOSolutionComparator
      • net.sf.jclec.mo.comparator.ConstrainedComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<net.sf.jclec.IIndividual>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NSGA2ConstrainedComparator

    public class ConstrainedComparator
extends MOSolutionComparator
    Compare two solutions in a problem with constraints. By default, this comparator establishes that two infeasible individuals are equals. If both individuals are feasible, then the fitness comparator is invoked.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    • Method Detail

      • compare

        public int compare(net.sf.jclec.IIndividual arg0,
                   net.sf.jclec.IIndividual arg1)
        Compare two individuals. By default, the following comparisons are made:
        • If one individual is feasible and the other is infeasible, the first is preferred.
        • If both individuals are infeasible, they are equal.
        • If both individuals are feasible, compare them by fitness.
        Specified by:
        compare in interface java.util.Comparator<net.sf.jclec.IIndividual>

        arg1 - Second individual
